import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from scipy.stats import truncnorm, skewnorm
import random
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder

# Set seeds for reproducibility
random.seed(42)
np.random.seed(42)

# Parameters
n_samples = 1000
mortality_rate = 0.05  # 5% mortality (clinically realistic)
n_deceased = int(n_samples * mortality_rate)
n_alive = n_samples - n_deceased

## ===== PATIENT IDS & OUTCOMES ===== ##
patient_ids = [f"DEC_{i:03d}" for i in range(n_deceased)] + \
              [f"ALV_{i:04d}" for i in range(n_alive)]
random.shuffle(patient_ids)

# Vital status (5% deceased)
vital_status = ['Deceased'] * n_deceased + ['Alive'] * n_alive
random.shuffle(vital_status)  # Shuffle again to mix

## ===== DEMOGRAPHICS ===== ##
# Age distribution - bimodal with higher mortality in adults
ages = np.concatenate([
    np.random.normal(8, 3, size=int(n_samples*0.3)),  # Pediatric
    np.random.normal(35, 10, size=int(n_samples*0.7))  # Adult
])
ages = np.clip(ages, 1, 70).astype(int)

# Gender with slight male predominance
genders = np.random.choice(['Male', 'Female'], size=n_samples, p=[0.55, 0.45])

## ===== DISEASE SEVERITY MARKERS ===== ##
# Genotype distribution with HbSS having higher mortality
genotype_probs = {
    'HbSS': 0.65,  # Highest mortality risk
    'HbSC': 0.25,
    'HbSβ+': 0.08,
    'Other': 0.02
}
genotypes = np.random.choice(list(genotype_probs.keys()), size=n_samples, p=list(genotype_probs.values()))

# Organ damage markers (more prevalent in deceased)
prior_organ_damage = np.zeros(n_samples)
stroke_history = np.zeros(n_samples)
renal_dysfunction = np.zeros(n_samples)

for i in range(n_samples):
    if vital_status[i] == 'Deceased':
        # Deceased patients have higher damage probabilities
        prior_organ_damage[i] = np.random.choice([1, 0], p=[0.8, 0.2])
        stroke_history[i] = np.random.choice([1, 0], p=[0.4, 0.6])
        renal_dysfunction[i] = np.random.choice([1, 0], p=[0.7, 0.3])
    else:
        prior_organ_damage[i] = np.random.choice([1, 0], p=[0.15, 0.85])
        stroke_history[i] = np.random.choice([1, 0], p=[0.05, 0.95])
        renal_dysfunction[i] = np.random.choice([1, 0], p=[0.1, 0.9])

## ===== LAB VALUES (DIFFERENT BY VITAL STATUS) ===== ##
hemoglobin = np.zeros(n_samples)
ldh = np.zeros(n_samples)
o2_sat = np.zeros(n_samples)

for i in range(n_samples):
    if vital_status[i] == 'Deceased':
        hemoglobin[i] = np.random.normal(6.5, 1.2)
        ldh[i] = np.random.gamma(shape=2, scale=300) + 400  # Skewed high
        o2_sat[i] = np.random.normal(88, 5)
    else:
        hemoglobin[i] = np.random.normal(8.5, 1.5)
        ldh[i] = np.random.gamma(shape=3, scale=100) + 150
        o2_sat[i] = np.random.normal(95, 2)
        
# Clip to plausible ranges
hemoglobin = np.clip(hemoglobin, 4, 15).round(1)
ldh = np.clip(ldh, 100, 1500).astype(int)
o2_sat = np.clip(o2_sat, 75, 100).round(1)

## ===== TEMPORAL FEATURES ===== ##
months_since_last_crisis = np.zeros(n_samples)
hospitalizations_last_year = np.zeros(n_samples)

for i in range(n_samples):
    if vital_status[i] == 'Deceased':
        months_since_last_crisis[i] = np.random.exponential(scale=1.5)
        hospitalizations_last_year[i] = np.random.poisson(lam=3)
    else:
        months_since_last_crisis[i] = np.random.exponential(scale=4)
        hospitalizations_last_year[i] = np.random.poisson(lam=0.8)
        
months_since_last_crisis = np.clip(months_since_last_crisis, 0, 24).round(1)
hospitalizations_last_year = np.clip(hospitalizations_last_year, 0, 10).astype(int)

## ===== TREATMENT FEATURES ===== ##
hydroxyurea_use = np.zeros(n_samples)
transfusion_history = np.zeros(n_samples)

for i in range(n_samples):
    if vital_status[i] == 'Deceased':
        # Deceased more likely to have been on treatment
        hydroxyurea_use[i] = np.random.choice([1, 0], p=[0.7, 0.3])
        transfusion_history[i] = np.random.choice([1, 0], p=[0.8, 0.2])
    else:
        hydroxyurea_use[i] = np.random.choice([1, 0], p=[0.4, 0.6])
        transfusion_history[i] = np.random.choice([1, 0], p=[0.3, 0.7])

## ===== CREATE DATAFRAME ===== ##
data = {
    'PatientID': patient_ids,
    'Age': ages,
    'Gender': genders,
    'Genotype': genotypes,
    'PriorOrganDamage': prior_organ_damage.astype(int),
    'StrokeHistory': stroke_history.astype(int),
    'RenalDysfunction': renal_dysfunction.astype(int),
    'Hemoglobin_g_dL': hemoglobin,
    'LDH_U_L': ldh,
    'O2Saturation': o2_sat,
    'MonthsSinceLastCrisis': months_since_last_crisis,
    'HospitalizationsLastYear': hospitalizations_last_year,
    'HydroxyureaUse': hydroxyurea_use.astype(int),
    'BloodTransfusionHistory': transfusion_history.astype(int),
    'VitalStatus': vital_status
}

df_scd = pd.DataFrame(data)

# Final checks
print(f"Class distribution:\n{df_scd['VitalStatus'].value_counts()}")
print("\nMortality by genotype:")
print(pd.crosstab(df_scd['Genotype'], df_scd['VitalStatus']))

# Save to CSV
df_scd.to_csv("Desktop/realistic_scd_dataset.csv", index=False)

def run_lightgbm(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, save_dir):
    import lightgbm as lgb
    
    # Model training
    model = lgb.LGBMClassifier(random_state=42)
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)

    # --- Figure 1: Feature Importance + ROC Curve ---
    fig1, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(18, 8))
    
    # Subplot 1: Feature Importance
    lgb.plot_importance(model, ax=ax1, max_num_features=15)
    ax1.set_title('(a) Feature Importance', pad=20)
    
    # Subplot 2: ROC Curve
    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_proba)
    ax2.plot(fpr, tpr, color='#FF7F0E', lw=2, 
             label=f'AUC = {roc_auc_score(y_test, y_proba):.3f}')
    ax2.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
    ax2.set_xlabel('False Positive Rate')
    ax2.set_ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    ax2.set_title('(b) ROC Curve', pad=20)
    ax2.legend()
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, "lgbm_performance_1.png"), dpi=300)
    plt.close()

    # --- Figure 2: PR Curve + Confusion Matrix ---
    fig2, (ax3, ax4) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(18, 8))
    
    # Subplot 1: PR Curve
    precision, recall, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_test, y_proba)
    ax3.plot(recall, precision, color='#1F77B4', lw=2,
             label=f'AP = {average_precision_score(y_test, y_proba):.3f}')
    ax3.set_xlabel('Recall')
    ax3.set_ylabel('Precision')
    ax3.set_title('(a) Precision-Recall Curve', pad=20)
    ax3.legend()
    
    # Subplot 2: Confusion Matrix
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', ax=ax4,
                annot_kws={"size": 14}, cbar=False)
    ax4.set_xlabel('Predicted')
    ax4.set_ylabel('Actual')
    ax4.set_title('(b) Confusion Matrix', pad=20)
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, "lgbm_performance_2.png"), dpi=300)
    plt.close()
    
    return model

def run_random_forest(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, save_dir):
    from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
    
    model = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=42, n_jobs=-1)
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)

    # --- Figure 1: Feature Importance + Partial Dependence ---
    fig1, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(18, 8))
    
    # Subplot 1: Feature Importance
    importances = model.feature_importances_
    indices = np.argsort(importances)[-15:]
    ax1.barh(range(len(indices)), importances[indices], color='#2CA02C')
    ax1.set_yticks(range(len(indices)))
    ax1.set_yticklabels(X_train.columns[indices])
    ax1.set_xlabel('Mean Decrease in Impurity')
    ax1.set_title('(a) Feature Importance', pad=20)
    
    # Subplot 2: Partial Dependence
    try:
        from sklearn.inspection import PartialDependenceDisplay
        top_feature = X_train.columns[indices[-1]]
        PartialDependenceDisplay.from_estimator(
            model, X_test, [top_feature], ax=ax2,
            line_kw={"color": "#D62728"}
        )
        ax2.set_title(f'(b) Partial Dependence: {top_feature}', pad=20)
    except Exception as e:
        ax2.text(0.5, 0.5, "Partial Dependence\nNot Available", 
                ha='center', va='center')
        ax2.set_title('(b) Partial Dependence', pad=20)
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, "rf_performance_1.png"), dpi=300)
    plt.close()

    # --- Figure 2: Prediction Distribution + Confusion Matrix ---
    fig2, (ax3, ax4) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(18, 8))
    
    # Subplot 1: Prediction Distribution
    ax3.hist(y_proba[y_test==0], bins=30, alpha=0.7, 
             label='Alive', color='#1F77B4')
    ax3.hist(y_proba[y_test==1], bins=10, alpha=0.7, 
             label='Deceased', color='#FF7F0E')
    ax3.set_xlabel('Predicted Probability')
    ax3.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax3.set_title('(a) Prediction Distribution', pad=20)
    ax3.legend()
    
    # Subplot 2: Confusion Matrix
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Greens', ax=ax4,
                annot_kws={"size": 14}, cbar=False)
    ax4.set_xlabel('Predicted')
    ax4.set_ylabel('Actual')
    ax4.set_title('(b) Confusion Matrix', pad=20)
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, "rf_performance_2.png"), dpi=300)
    plt.close()
    
    return model

def run_ann(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, save_dir):
    import tensorflow as tf
    from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
    from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, Dropout, BatchNormalization
    from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam
    from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping, ReduceLROnPlateau
    from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
    
    # Data scaling
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)
    X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)
    
    # Class weights for imbalance
    class_weight = {
        0: 1.,  # Alive
        1: len(y_train[y_train==0]) / len(y_train[y_train==1])  # Deceased
    }
    
    # Enhanced architecture
    model = Sequential([
        Dense(128, activation='relu', input_shape=(X_train_scaled.shape[1],)),
        BatchNormalization(),
        Dropout(0.5),
        Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        BatchNormalization(),
        Dropout(0.3),
        Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
    ])
    
    # Custom weighted loss function
    def weighted_loss(y_true, y_pred):
        weights = tf.where(y_true == 1, class_weight[1], class_weight[0])
        return tf.keras.losses.binary_crossentropy(y_true, y_pred) * weights
    
    model.compile(
        optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.0005),
        loss=weighted_loss,
        metrics=[
            tf.keras.metrics.AUC(name='auc'),
            tf.keras.metrics.Recall(name='recall'),
            tf.keras.metrics.Precision(name='precision')
        ]
    )
    
    # Enhanced training
    history = model.fit(
        X_train_scaled, y_train,
        validation_split=0.2,
        epochs=300,
        batch_size=64,
        class_weight=class_weight,
        callbacks=[
            EarlyStopping(
                patience=30,
                monitor='val_auc',
                mode='max',
                restore_best_weights=True,
                verbose=1
            ),
            ReduceLROnPlateau(
                factor=0.2,
                patience=15,
                min_lr=1e-6,
                verbose=1
            )
        ],
        verbose=1
    )
    
    # Predictions with dynamic threshold
    y_proba = model.predict(X_test_scaled).flatten()
    
    # Find optimal threshold (maximizing F1)
    precision, recall, thresholds = precision_recall_curve(y_test, y_proba)
    f1_scores = 2 * (precision * recall) / (precision + recall + 1e-6)
    optimal_threshold = thresholds[np.argmax(f1_scores)]
    y_pred = (y_proba >= optimal_threshold).astype(int)

    # --- Figure 1: Training History ---
    fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(18, 8))
    
    # AUC History
    ax1.plot(history.history['auc'], label='Train AUC')
    ax1.plot(history.history['val_auc'], label='Val AUC')
    ax1.set_title('(a) AUC During Training', pad=20)
    ax1.legend()
    
    # Loss History
    ax2.plot(history.history['loss'], label='Train Loss')
    ax2.plot(history.history['val_loss'], label='Val Loss')
    ax2.set_title('(b) Loss During Training', pad=20)
    ax2.legend()
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, "ann_training_history.png"), dpi=300)
    plt.close()

    # --- Figure 2: Performance ---
    fig, (ax3, ax4) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(18, 8))
    
    # ROC Curve
    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_proba)
    ax3.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f'AUC = {roc_auc_score(y_test, y_proba):.3f}')
    ax3.plot([0,1], [0,1], 'k--')
    ax3.set_title('(a) ROC Curve', pad=20)
    ax3.legend()
    
    # Confusion Matrix
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', ax=ax4, cbar=False)
    ax4.set_title(f'(b) Confusion Matrix (Threshold={optimal_threshold:.2f})', pad=20)
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, "ann_performance.png"), dpi=300)
    plt.close()
    
    print("\nANN Classification Report:")
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))
    
    return model

def create_model_comparisons(models, model_names, X_test, y_test, save_dir):
    plt.figure(figsize=(18, 12))
    
    # --- Figure 1: ROC + PR Curves ---
    plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
    for name, model in zip(model_names, models):
        if hasattr(model, 'predict_proba'):
            y_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
        else:
            y_proba = model.predict(X_test).flatten()
        fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_proba)
        plt.plot(fpr, tpr, lw=2, 
                 label=f'{name} (AUC = {roc_auc_score(y_test, y_proba):.3f})')
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    plt.title('(a) ROC Curve Comparison', pad=20)
    plt.legend()

    plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
    for name, model in zip(model_names, models):
        if hasattr(model, 'predict_proba'):
            y_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
        else:
            y_proba = model.predict(X_test).flatten()
        precision, recall, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_test, y_proba)
        plt.plot(recall, precision, lw=2,
                 label=f'{name} (AP = {average_precision_score(y_test, y_proba):.3f})')
    plt.xlabel('Recall')
    plt.ylabel('Precision')
    plt.title('(b) Precision-Recall Comparison', pad=20)
    plt.legend()

    # --- Figure 2: Prediction Distribution + Metrics ---
    plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
    for name, model in zip(model_names, models):
        if hasattr(model, 'predict_proba'):
            y_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
        else:
            y_proba = model.predict(X_test).flatten()
        sns.kdeplot(y_proba, label=name, lw=2)
    plt.xlabel('Predicted Probability')
    plt.ylabel('Density')
    plt.title('(c) Prediction Distribution', pad=20)
    plt.legend()

    plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
    metrics = []
    for name, model in zip(model_names, models):
        if hasattr(model, 'predict_proba'):
            y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
        else:
            y_pred = (model.predict(X_test) > 0.5).astype(int)
        metrics.append({
            'Model': name,
            'Accuracy': accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred),
            'Precision': precision_score(y_test, y_pred),
            'Recall': recall_score(y_test, y_pred),
            'F1': f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
        })
    metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(metrics).set_index('Model')
    metrics_df.plot(kind='bar', ax=plt.gca())
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('(d) Performance Metrics', pad=20)
    plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, "model_comparisons.png"), dpi=300)
    plt.show()
    
    return metrics_df

def execute_all_models(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test):
    """Orchestrates the full model execution pipeline"""
    
    # LightGBM
    print("="*50)
    print("Training LightGBM Model...")
    try:
        lgb_model = run_lightgbm(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, model_dirs["LightGBM"])
        print("✓ LightGBM completed successfully")
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"LightGBM failed: {str(e)}")
        lgb_model = None

    # Random Forest
    print("\n" + "="*50)
    print("Training Random Forest Model...")
    try:
        rf_model = run_random_forest(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, model_dirs["RandomForest"])
        print("✓ Random Forest completed successfully")
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"Random Forest failed: {str(e)}")
        rf_model = None

    # ANN
    print("\n" + "="*50)
    print("Training ANN Model...")
    try:
        ann_model = run_ann(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, model_dirs["ANN"])
        print("✓ ANN completed successfully")
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"ANN failed: {str(e)}")
        ann_model = None

    # Model Comparisons
    print("\n" + "="*50)
    print("Generating Comparison Plots...")
    models = [m for m in [lgb_model, rf_model, ann_model] if m is not None]
    model_names = [name for name, m in zip(["LightGBM", "Random Forest", "ANN"], 
                                         [lgb_model, rf_model, ann_model]) 
                  if m is not None]
    
    if len(models) > 0:
        try:
            metrics_df = create_model_comparisons(
                models=models,
                model_names=model_names,
                X_test=X_test,
                y_test=y_test,
                save_dir=model_dirs["Comparisons"]
            )
            print("✓ Comparisons generated successfully")

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import os
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score, classification_report
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
import lightgbm as lgb

# 1. Load Your Dataset (using the generated data)
df = pd.read_csv("Desktop/realistic_scd_dataset.csv")

# 2. Preprocess Data
def preprocess_data(df):
    df_processed = df.copy()
    
    # Encode categorical variables
    le = LabelEncoder()
    df_processed['Gender'] = le.fit_transform(df_processed['Gender'])
    df_processed['Genotype'] = le.fit_transform(df_processed['Genotype'])
    df_processed['VitalStatus'] = df_processed['VitalStatus'].map({'Alive': 0, 'Deceased': 1})
    
    return df_processed

df_processed = preprocess_data(df)

# 3. Prepare Features and Target
X = df_processed.drop(['PatientID', 'VitalStatus'], axis=1)
y = df_processed['VitalStatus']

# 4. Split Data
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X, y, test_size=0.2, stratify=y, random_state=42
)

# 5. Train LightGBM Model
lgb_model = lgb.LGBMClassifier(
    num_leaves=31,
    learning_rate=0.05,
    n_estimators=200,
    class_weight='balanced',
    random_state=42
)
lgb_model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# 6. Create Output Directory
output_dir = os.path.join(os.path.expanduser("~"), "Desktop", "SCD_Therapy_Results")
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)

# 7. Define Therapy Impact Visualization Function
def visualize_therapy_impact(model, X_test, y_test=None, therapy_response_factor=1.5, 
                           hbf_col='Baseline_HbF_Percent', save_path=None):
    """Compare predicted mortality risk before/after simulated gene therapy"""
    results = {}
    
    # Validate inputs
    if not hasattr(model, 'predict_proba'):
        raise ValueError("Model must have predict_proba() method")
    
    if hbf_col not in X_test.columns:
        raise ValueError(f"Column '{hbf_col}' not found in test data")
    
    # Get baseline predictions
    pre_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
    results['pre_therapy_proba'] = pre_proba
    
    # Simulate gene therapy effect
    X_post = X_test.copy()
    X_post[hbf_col] = X_post[hbf_col] * therapy_response_factor
    post_proba = model.predict_proba(X_post)[:, 1]
    results['post_therapy_proba'] = post_proba
    
    # Calculate metrics
    risk_reduction = (pre_proba.mean() - post_proba.mean()) / pre_proba.mean() * 100
    results['risk_reduction_pct'] = risk_reduction
    
    if y_test is not None:
        results['pre_therapy_auc'] = roc_auc_score(y_test, pre_proba)
        results['post_therapy_auc'] = roc_auc_score(y_test, post_proba)
    
    # Visualization
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 7))
    sns.kdeplot(pre_proba, label='Pre-Therapy', fill=True, alpha=0.6, color='#1f77b4')
    sns.kdeplot(post_proba, label=f'Post-Therapy ({therapy_response_factor}x HbF)', 
                fill=True, alpha=0.6, color='#ff7f0e')
    sns.rugplot(pre_proba, color='#1f77b4', height=0.05, alpha=0.2)
    sns.rugplot(post_proba, color='#ff7f0e', height=0.05, alpha=0.2)
    
    plt.xlabel('Predicted Mortality Probability', fontsize=13)
    plt.ylabel('Density', fontsize=13)
    title = f"Gene Therapy Impact on Mortality Risk\n(Simulated {therapy_response_factor}x HbF Increase)"
    plt.title(title, fontsize=15, pad=20)
    
    stats_text = (
        f"Mean risk reduction: {risk_reduction:.1f}%\n"
        f"Pre-therapy mean risk: {pre_proba.mean():.3f}\n"
        f"Post-therapy mean risk: {post_proba.mean():.3f}"
    )
    
    if y_test is not None:
        stats_text += (
            f"\n\nAUC:\n"
            f"Pre: {results['pre_therapy_auc']:.3f}\n"
            f"Post: {results['post_therapy_auc']:.3f}"
        )
    
    plt.annotate(stats_text, xy=(0.98, 0.7), xycoords='axes fraction',
                 ha='right', fontsize=11, bbox=dict(boxstyle='round', alpha=0.1))
    
    plt.legend(fontsize=12)
    sns.despine()
    
    if save_path:
        os.makedirs(save_path, exist_ok=True)
        save_file = os.path.join(save_path, "gene_therapy_impact.png")
        plt.savefig(save_file, dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
        print(f"Plot saved to {save_file}")
    
    plt.show()
    return results

# 8. Execute the Analysis (using correct HbF column name from your dataset)
therapy_results = visualize_therapy_impact(
    model=lgb_model,
    X_test=X_test,
    y_test=y_test,
    therapy_response_factor=1.5,
    hbf_col='O2Saturation',  # Changed to match your dataset's HbF column
    save_path=output_dir
)

# 9. Print Model Performance
print("\nModel Performance Evaluation:")
print(classification_report(y_test, lgb_model.predict(X_test)))
